article_title: Royal Palm condo awash in foreclosures; fifth guilty plea issued
article_text:
Dec. 26– A Miami attorney is the fifth person to plead guilty to criminal charges stemming from a $25 million mortgage scheme that left a Royal Palm Beach community flooded with foreclosures. Federal prosecutors say Rashmi Airan-Pace, 43, was the closing agent on 90 sales at the Kensington of Royal Palm Beach condominium between 2007 and 2009 where hefty buyer…
